author: TheGDC33
body: I can see your comments and tell you would be considered a troll by many. I would argue you are just uninformed on the cycles and the movement of Memecoins. You came for massive gains but weren't informed (research and reading) enough to understand you will also have to likely suffer massive drawdowns. That part is on you. This is a painful and crazy game and I am not sure I am having fun with price action but I do love the community and I know the assignment. This is what I signed up for. Don't buy the ticket if you can't handle the ride.  I wish you well in your investing arc. You can always select something way way safer. BTC is a great option if you want crypto or just mutual funds

author: TheGDC33
body: Yeah well I wish I had been willing to listen to others or more importantly I wish I knew how to properly track transactions and wallet watch myself or at least done more digging when the Doxx happened, but I couldn't and didn't.   Kendu is stronger than ever and I have no doubt that we will make some really positive moves when the market actually turns with a positive sentiment and an injection of liquidity into more risky assets. Maybe even some QE and whatever else can turn this ship around for good. Time will tell, but that shit really did suck, but it is over now and we have moved on and are better than ever.

author: TheGDC33
body: I stand by my comment. This is how memecoins move and crypto is extremely volatile overall. Look up the price action of SHIB from last cycle or even how Pepe started...same thing, just massive draw downs. That doesn't mean it happens with every coin because the market is saturated with garbage. But it is fact and it isn't just lightning striking.  https://preview.redd.it/4eqfomzx32ne1.jpeg?width=1050&format=pjpg&auto=webp&s=a04d9f89ba9ef4892e88c72b9a5599c77cc1e58f  Better if you find the PEPE chart yourself. Good luck with your investments though, plenty of options

author: p0tatemoon
body: Seems like you are describing 99% of the memecoins  Kendu does have a value which puts it in the 1%. To know the value, one will have to DYOR. If a person doesn't see the value then it is ok the leave Kendu on the side and continue to search for another investment   As I always say, memecoins are a high risk high reward investment. DYOR is mandatory. If someone doesn't believe in the project, please cut the losses and invest in something you have properly done your research and believe in  I believe in Kendu, only time will tell if I was right or wrong. Meanwhile, I'll continue to contribute my way to the project
